LESSON ID: l-053-2
TITLE: An-Najm Part 2:
The Heavenly Journey and Divine Signs
METADATA: Mecca - Ayahs 13 - 24
SUMMARY: 

--- LESSON STORY / EXPLANATION TEXT ---
In this part of Surah An-Najm, Allah describes a heavenly vision beyond imagination. The Prophet Muhammad ﷺ was shown the greatest signs of his Lord and saw Angel Jibrīl in his true form.
These verses teach us the Prophet’s honor and perfect manners during divine revelation.
According to <i>Tafsīr Ibn Kathīr</i> and <i>Al-Qurṭubī</i>, these verses describe the Prophet’s ﷺ <b>second vision of Angel Jibrīl</b>during his heavenly ascension (<i>Mi‘rāj</i>). Jibrīl appeared in his true form vast and radiant, with wings filling the horizon. The Prophet ﷺ reached <i>Sidrat al-Muntahā</i>, the Lote Tree of the Utmost Boundary, where all created knowledge ends.
Beyond this boundary, only Allah knows what lies ahead. Ibn Kathīr explains that this tree is covered with divine light and indescribable colors, showing the beauty of Allah’s creation. Near it lies <i>Jannat al-Ma’wā</i>, the Garden of Rest, reminding believers that Paradise is already prepared for them.
Let's explore this theme together and see what it teaches us about divine signs and proper behavior in Allah's presence.
These verses reveal the Prophet’s ﷺ heavenly vision, showing real signs, not illusions. They remind us to stay humble before Allah’s mysteries and follow the true revelation He sent.
🌗 <b>Coming next: </b>The Heavenly Journey and Divine Signs

