As we conclude Surah ‘Abasa, we witness a powerful scene the Day of Judgment, <i>As-Sakhkhah</i>, the Deafening Blast.
On that day, even the closest family members will run from each other.
Through these verses, Allah SWT reminds us to prepare for the Day when only deeds will matter.
These verses describe <i>As-Sakhkhah</i> the great, deafening sound that will signal the start of the Day of Judgment.
On that Day, every relationship will fade as each soul faces its own record of deeds. Parents, siblings, and children will be forgotten in the rush of accountability.
The Prophet Muhammad ﷺ explained that people will be gathered barefoot and uncovered, yet no one will notice others, as everyone will be concerned only with themselves. This Day is not described to frighten, but to awaken reminding us that only faith, good deeds, and sincerity will bring light and peace to our faces when we meet Allah SWT.
Let's read the ayah...
Let's learn some words from this surah. To memorize, repeat each word three times with its meaning.
These verses remind us that on the Final Day, family ties and worldly status will vanish.
Only faith and deeds will endure.
Surah ‘Abasa closes with a call to prepare for that meeting to live sincerely so our faces shine with peace before Allah SWT.

